n our T-P profile, thereby\nindicating that the inversion at high altitude is model-dependent. Despite no\ndistinct features, the analysis done on CoRoT-1 b paves the way to\nhigh-precision results with stare mode spectroscopy. As a new generation of\nobservations from the James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) approaches, CoRoT-1 b\nmight be an interesting follow-up target because the time-series spectroscopic\nmodes of JWST's NIRSpec, MIRI, and NIRCam instruments will be analogous to\nHST's stare mode.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jun 2022 18:03:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-01"}
