sion measure (DM) variations of $\\Delta{\\rm\nDM} >1$ pc cm$^{-3}$ on month-to-year timescales, we determine that FRB\n20200120E's DM has remained stable ($\\Delta{\\rm DM} <0.15$ pc cm$^{-3}$) over\n$>10$ months. Overall, the observational characteristics of FRB 20200120E\ndeviate quantitatively from other active repeaters, but it is unclear whether\nit is qualitatively a different type of source.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jun 2022 09:08:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Jan 2023 23:49:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-08"}
